  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the wok to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together the aquafaba, soy milk, baking powder, and coconut sugar until smooth.",
    "Add the salt, black pepper, shortening, cornstarch, soy flour, lemon zest, and lemon juice to the bowl. Whisk until combined.",
    "Pour the mixture into the preheated wok and cook for 20-25 minutes, or until the edge is golden brown and the center is set.",
    "Remove the wok from the oven and let cool for 5 minutes before slicing and serving."
  ],
